                     <interp inst="t17751206-1-person185" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's.</p>
               <p>Did she say any thing to you? - I do not immediately recollect that she did: she expressed a wish that he might be sent for: I sent a message to Mr. Perreau at Sir Thomas Frankland's,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177512060016"></xptr> to tell him that a patient wanted him, and to desire him to call at home first.</p>
               <p>Was that your own thought, or did any body tell you to bid the messenger tell him that? - I think it was my own thought.</p>
               <p>Did you mention this message in Mrs. Rudd's hearing? - She was there.</p>
               <p>Did she say any thing? - I don't recollect that she did: she seemed to wait for him with great impatience: she said she should be too late, but did not mention the place.</p>
               <p>Did she say any thing when you desired Mr. Perreau to be told a patient wanted him? - She desired that he might call at home first.</p>
               <p>Do you remember Mr. 
               <persName id="t17751206-1-person186">
                  Robert
                   Perreau
               <interp inst="t17751206-1-person186" type="surname" value="Perreau"></interp>
