                     <interp inst="t17751206-1-person194" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who had never borrowed money for seventeen years, should want 9000 l. in May 1774? - There were 13,000 l. in the whole.</p>
               <p>For what purpose was this money wanted if there were no losses to settle? - 
               <persName id="t17751206-1-person195">
                  Robert
                   Perreau
               <interp inst="t17751206-1-person195" type="surname" value="Perreau"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17751206-1-person195" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17751206-1-person195" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             always told me that his brother Daniel had married a woman intimately connected with Mr. Adair, and that he was paying her fortune by instalments.</p>
